
A:
	We are lost in this cave. How much more battery power do we have left?

B:
	You rail at them
  Because you have no children of your own.

A:
	I am very much obliged, dear Mr. Aslaksen, (Shakes hands
with him.) Goodbye, goodbye.

B:
	I see, thou hast still a request to make of me. I pray thee, speak!

A:
	How much food do we have left? I'm beginning to worry.

B:
	Father, forgive me for all that
I have neglected to do! You shall see how I will try and make up for it!
How hard I shall work!

A:
	Pastor, do you know who and what I am?

B:
	Not you at any rate.

A:
	Look! Is that a shaft of light I see?

B:
	_Vast subterranean crypts_. ALLADINE _and_ PALOMIDES.

A:
	Dark and dirty.

B:
	Dark and dirty.

A:
	Hooray! We've escaped!

B:
	Yes, you must stay in the house.

A:
	Falk, you mean.

B:
	The agreement between us is sealed with word and
with hand,--many honorable men whom I see here can bear witness
to that: Olaf, my son, was to wed your daughter; tomorrow at my
house the wedding was to be held--
